    <text type="note" xml:lang="ru" xml:id="letter-09062"> 
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when-custom="1788-06-28">1788 г. июня 28.</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Реляция для чтения в <rs ref="places.xml#pie01">церкви</rs> при молебне в <date when-custom="1788-06-30">пятницу</date>.—Объявление <name type="event" ref="events.xml#swedi02">войны</name>, <title ref="works.xml#manife05">манифест</title>— поспеет ли к <date when-custom="1788-07-02">воскресенью</date>?
                <note type="editorial">
                    A.V. Khrapovitskii notes in his diary under <date when-custom="1788-06-30">June 30 1788</date> that Catherine signed the <title ref="works.xml#manife05">manifesto</title> about the <name type="event" ref="events.xml#swedi02">war against <placeName ref="places.xml#swe01">Sweden</placeName></name> and later went to the church service for the victory on <placeName ref="places.xml#dni02">Liman</placeName> on <date when="1788-06-17">June 17 1788</date> in the <placeName ref="places.xml#pie01">Cathedral of Saint Peter and Saint Paul</placeName>. On <date when-custom="1788-07-02">July 2 1788</date> the manifesto was read in what was at the time the <placeName ref="places.xml#stm01">Summer Palace</placeName> and then became the <placeName ref="places.xml#stm01">Saint Michael's Castle</placeName> (
                    <bibl>
                        <title ref="works.xml#dnevni02">Dnevnik A.V. Khrapovitskago s 18 ianvaria 1782 po 17 sentiabria 1793 goda</title>
                        , <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 57-58.</biblScope>
                    </bibl>
                    ).
                </note>
            </p>
        </body>
